CHANGES_REQUIRED

1. `ui/backend/services/meshing_gmsh/gmsh_runner.py:203,212-236` — P1  
R9’s new heuristic still leaves a write-time backend fault misclassified as `GmshMeshGenerationError` / `gmsh_diverged` / 4xx when `gmsh.write()` raises plain `Exception` for reasons that do not change `os.access(output_dir, W_OK)` or directory existence, most notably `ENOSPC` / disk-full. That is exactly the class this chain is trying to close.  
Suggested fix: `Wrap gmsh.write(str(output_msh_path)) in its own try/except Exception block and re-raise write-time failures as OSError (or FileNotFoundError for a vanished parent) instead of routing them through the generic geometry-failure catch-all.`

2. `ui/backend/services/meshing_gmsh/to_foam.py:208-213` — P2  
Inside the “best-effort log copy” fallback, `log_dest.write_text(...)` can itself raise `OSError` if `case_host_dir` vanished, the filesystem is read-only, or the disk is full. That escapes as a raw uncaught 5xx with no `GmshToFoamError` contract.  
Suggested fix: `Inside the except Exception fallback for log retrieval, wrap log_dest.write_text(...) in try/except OSError and raise GmshToFoamError(f"failed to persist fallback gmshToFoam log: {exc}") from exc (or skip the write entirely and keep an in-memory placeholder path/message).`

I would not close the chain on `bb56ce5` yet.
